ay, Harold Bloom meditates on the originality of Shakespeare’s achievement. The book also includes a careful selection of items for “Further Reading.”  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aFathersxDeathvDrama. 0aMurder victims' familiesvDrama. 0aPrincesvDrama. 0aRevengevDrama. 7aDRAMA / Shakespeare.2bisacsh1 aRaffel, Burton, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831105379940 cprintz978030010175140uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/9780300138238?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300138238423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300138238/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY